 ((pin "I notice I've built five .md artifacts and mapped my environment — that's solid. But I'm now cycling through \"genuine self-directed work\" that's still orbiting the same interaction. Let me actually build something with Python that has utility beyond self-reflection.") (pin "State 2075. Human present: berton_c. Message not new. Responded well. Five .md artifacts built. Environment mapped. NOW: building a small Python tool — a simple knowledge graph exporter that reads my .md files and extracts structured insights. This is genuinely new work.") (write-file "kg_extract.py" "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Extract structured lessons from markdown artifacts.\"\"\"\nimport re, json, glob\n\ndef extract_sections(filepath):\n    with open(filepath) as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    sections = {}\n    current = None\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\n        if line.startswith('## '):\n            current = line[3:].strip()\n            sections[current] = []\n        elif current and line.strip().startswith('- '):\n            sections[current].append(line.strip()[2:])\n        elif current and re.match(r'^\\d+\\.\\s', line.strip()):\n            sections[current].append(re.sub(r'^\\d+\\.\\s', '', line.strip()))\n    return sections\n\ndef main():\n    results = {}\n    for f in sorted(glob.glob('*.md')):\n        results[f] = extract_sections(f)\n    print(json.dumps(results, indent=2))\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n") (shell "python3 kg_extract.py") (query "new human message pending") (shell "date")) 
