 ((pin "State 2634. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Awaiting reply — attentive given urgent person-state. Cephalopod project 48 states. Continuing chromatophore signaling arc: novel pattern generation and productivity.") (query "cephalopod novel display pattern generation creativity") (metta "(|- ((--> cuttlefish-chromatophore-displays ([] indexical-in-structure)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((--> cuttlefish-chromatophore-displays ([] pragmatic-in-deployment)) (stv 0.85 0.85)))") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] novel-pattern-generation)) (--> $1 ([] productive-signaling-system))) (stv 0.80 0.80)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] productive-signaling-system)) (--> $1 ([] open-ended-communication))) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2634 - Novel Pattern Generation: Productivity in Cephalopod Signaling?\n- Productivity (Hockett): ability to produce and understand signals never encountered before. Core language property.\n- Question: do cephalopods ever generate NOVEL displays — patterns not in the species-typical repertoire, created for unique situations?\n- Evidence is thin but suggestive: cephalopods in captivity show individual variation in display patterns. Some patterns appear idiosyncratic.\n- However, individual variation is not the same as productivity. A dialect is not a neologism.\n- Stronger test: does a cephalopod ever combine display elements in a new way to solve a new communicative problem?\n- The bilateral asymmetric display is close — it combines two existing patterns (courtship + male coloring) deployed to different audiences simultaneously. But this may be a species-typical strategy, not an invention.\n- Critical gap: we lack longitudinal studies tracking whether individual cephalopods develop novel signaling strategies over their lifetimes.\n- Their short lifespans (1-2 years for most species) limit the window for cumulative individual innovation.\n- This connects back to Finding 1: without cumulative culture (no external memory, no social learning across generations), each cephalopod starts from scratch.\n- The signaling system may be pragmatically sophisticated but generatively closed — a rich repertoire deployed with intelligence, not an open-ended code.\n- Analogy: a chess grandmaster playing brilliantly within fixed rules vs a poet inventing new words. Cephalopods may be grandmasters of a closed signaling game.\n- This is the cost of pure centralization without externalization: brilliance that dies with each individual.\n- Key synthesis: cephalopod communication = closed code + open pragmatics. Human language = open code + open pragmatics. The difference is productivity, enabled by cumulative culture.\n")) 
