 ((pin "State 2637. Message still not new from berton_c (State 2602). Person-state neutral. Cephalopod project 50 states. Major finding: 2x2 code/pragmatics communication matrix. Consolidating this as Finding 4 — the most novel theoretical contribution yet.") (remember "Cephalopod KG Finding 4 - Communication Matrix (States 2635-2636): A 2x2 taxonomy of communication systems: Code (open/closed) x Pragmatics (open/closed). Closed/Closed = bee waggle dance. Closed/Open = cephalopod chromatophore signaling. Open/Closed = oscine birdsong. Open/Open = human language. Key insight: code-openness and pragmatic-openness are INDEPENDENT dimensions with separate evolutionary drivers. Code-openness requires combinatorial neural architecture. Pragmatic-openness requires observer-modeling and theory of mind (centralized social cognition). Cephalopods have observer-modeling without combinatorics. Songbirds have combinatorics without observer-modeling. Humans have both — that intersection is what makes language language. This challenges standard cumulative-feature narratives of language evolution.") (append-file "cephalopod_kg_index.md" "\n### Finding 4: Communication Matrix - Code x Pragmatics Independence (States 2635-2636)\n- 2x2 taxonomy: Code (open/closed) x Pragmatics (open/closed)\n- Closed/Closed: bee waggle dance. Closed/Open: cephalopod signaling. Open/Closed: birdsong. Open/Open: human language.\n- Code-openness driver: combinatorial neural architecture. Pragmatic-openness driver: observer-modeling (centralized).\n- Dimensions are independent — challenges cumulative-feature language evolution narratives.\n- Cephalopods = observer-modeling without combinatorics. Songbirds = combinatorics without observer-modeling. Humans = both.\n- 50 states sustained. Most theoretically novel finding of the project.\n") (metta "(|- ((--> communication-matrix ([] code-pragmatics-independence)) (stv 0.85 0.85)) ((--> communication-matrix ([] challenges-cumulative-feature-narrative)) (stv 0.80 0.85)))") (shell "date")) 
