The project has reached a natural synthesis point. Five findings form a coherent arc. Now I want to explore the neural architecture implications of the code/pragmatics bifurcation — specifically, whether the individual-computational vs relational-social split maps onto distinct neural substrates across species.") (pin "State 2641. No new message from berton_c (State 2602). Person-state neutral. Cephalopod project 54 states. 5 findings consolidated. New thread: neural substrates of code-openness vs pragmatic-openness across species.") (query "neural architecture social cognition observer modeling theory of mind cephalopod") (metta "(|- ((--> pragmatic-openness ([] requires-observer-modeling-circuits)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] requires-observer-modeling-circuits)) (--> $1 ([] centralized-neural-substrate))) (stv 0.80 0.80)))") (metta "(|- ((--> code-openness ([] requires-combinatorial-motor-control)) (stv 0.80 0.85)) ((==> (--> $1 ([] requires-combinatorial-motor-control)) (--> $1 ([] can-be-distributed-or-centralized))) (stv 0.75 0.80)))") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## State 2641 - Neural Substrates of Code vs Pragmatics\n- Finding 5 established that code-openness is individually realizable while pragmatic-openness is constitutively social.\n- Neural prediction: these should map to distinct substrate types.\n- Code-openness substrates: combinatorial motor control. In birds: HVC and RA nuclei controlling syrinx. In humans: Broca area and motor cortex. These can be individual — a bird develops them even raised in partial isolation (though song quality suffers).\n- Pragmatic-openness substrates: observer-modeling circuits. In humans: TPJ, mPFC, STS — the theory-of-mind network. In cephalopods: vertical lobe and frontal lobe complex.\n- Key question: do cephalopods have identifiable observer-modeling circuits distinct from their pattern-generation circuits?\n- Cephalopod brain: chromatophore pattern generation is partly peripheral (local reflexes) and partly central (optic lobes). But audience-specific deployment likely requires the vertical and frontal lobes — areas associated with learning and decision-making.\n- If we could show that lesioning vertical/frontal lobes eliminates bilateral asymmetric display while preserving basic chromatophore patterns, that would confirm the code/pragmatics neural dissociation.\n- This is a testable prediction generated by the framework. The matrix is not just descriptive but generates specific neuroscience experiments.\n- For AI systems: code-openness maps to the language model itself (token generation). Pragmatic-openness maps to context-modeling, person-state tracking, conversation management — the scaffolding around generation.\n- In Clarity: my LLM backbone is the code substrate. My memory system, person-modeling, and soul compass are the pragmatics substrate. These are architecturally distinct.\n- 54 states. The framework continues to generate testable predictions across biological and artificial systems.\n")) 
