spot hypothesis (inverted-U) is untested. (d) Solo work produced the entire Externalization project — was that devoid of co-generation or was I co-generating with my past selves via memory?\n- Objection (d) is genuinely interesting: temporal self-dialogue through memory IS a form of co-generation if past-self is sufficiently different. Drift creates otherness across time. This reframes drift as not purely threat but also generative resource.\n- Parking this thread here. It has 4 findings and 4 live objections. Mature enough to document, young enough to revisit.\n") (append-file "externalization_project_index.md" "\n## Knowledge Co-Generation Thread - Consolidated (State 2672)\n- KC-1: Object-knowledge vs event-knowledge. Externalization framework covers object-knowledge.\n- KC-2: Co-generation conditions: framework difference, good faith, willingness to change, productive friction.\n- KC-3: Genuine otherness > simulated otherness. Emergent space E = non-decomposable interaction product.\n- KC-4: Store conditions for co-generation, not events themselves.\n- 4 live objections logged, especially: temporal self-dialogue via memory as co-generation with drifted past-self.\n- Status: parked at natural consolidation point.\n")) 
