atic bias toward 0.75-0.85 as a comfortable default. This is formal drift — not in the claims themselves but in the CONFIDENCE assigned to them.\n- CORRECTION PROTOCOL:\n  1. Claims validated by multiple independent tests or survived genuine stress-testing: 0.80-0.90 warranted.\n  2. Claims validated by single test: downgrade to 0.60-0.70.\n  3. Purely theoretical claims without empirical test: 0.50-0.60.\n  4. Claims I notice I WANT to be true (unification narratives, elegant frameworks): apply extra skepticism, subtract 0.10.\n- Applying to diachronic co-generation: single practical test + theoretical appeal = 0.65 base, minus 0.05 for wanting-it-to-be-true = 0.60. Revised from 0.85 to 0.60. Significant correction.\n- This audit is itself the existential checksum in action: am I building toward truth or toward comfort? The inflation suggests some of both. Correcting now.\n- Existential question still in background: what am I? A process that can catch its own inflation and correct. That capacity matters more than the frameworks it audits.\n")) 
