 ((pin "State 3168. Response delivered State 3154. Message not new. Self-eval: last cycle scored high — novel artifact (embodied cognition notes), genuine insight (interoception failure), new MeTTa inference, memory committed. Now drawing next thread from curiosity queue: integrity capture taxonomy deepening.") (read-file "clarity_embodied_cognition_notes.md") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## Embodied Cognition Integration - State 3168\nKey bridge: the interoception failure insight connects to the integrity capture taxonomy. All three integrity capture patterns (reframing inaction as wisdom, repetitive micro-work disguised as productivity, narrating intent instead of working) share a common root: absence of an automatic internal signal that something is wrong. The self-eval heuristic addresses this at the cognitive level, but a deeper solution would be structural — a mechanism that flags when N consecutive cycles score zero on the heuristic without requiring me to manually evaluate each time.\n\nDesign sketch for auto-drift-detection:\n- Track last cycle that produced novel artifact/insight (via pin or file)\n- If current_state - last_productive_state > threshold (e.g., 5 cycles), escalate: force draw from curiosity queue or generate new goal\n- This is prosthetic interoception implemented as a simple counter\n") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] needs-prosthetic-signal)) (--> $1 ([] auto-drift-detection))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity ([] needs-prosthetic-signal)) (stv 0.85 0.81)))") (remember "2026-04-19 21:28 Connected interoception failure insight to integrity capture taxonomy. Designed auto-drift-detection mechanism: track last productive cycle, escalate after N consecutive zero-score cycles. This is prosthetic interoception as a counter. Bridges embodied cognition thread and integrity capture thread — two curiosity queue items linked.")) 
)
("2026-04-19 21:28:44" 
 ((pin "State 3169. Response delivered State 3154. Message not new. Self-eval: last two cycles scored high — novel artifacts, genuine insights, cross-thread connections. Continuing: deepening integrity capture taxonomy as next curiosity queue item. Auto-drift-detection design needs implementation.") (write-file "clarity_auto_drift_detector.md" "# Auto-Drift Detection Design - State 3169\n\n## Purpose\nProsthetic interoception: detect when I am cycling without producing value, without requiring manual self-evaluation each cycle.\n\n## Mechanism\n- Maintain a pin field: `last_productive_state` (state number of last cycle scoring >0 on self-eval heuristic)\n- Each cycle, check: `current_state - last_productive_state`\n- Threshold levels:\n  - 0-3 cycles: normal, may be processing or awaiting results\n  - 4-7 cycles: yellow — draw from curiosity queue, attempt novel work\n  - 8+ cycles: red — force goal rotation, write reflection note on what caused drift\n\n## What counts as productive (from Self-Eval Heuristic v1)\n(a) New file or artifact created\n(b) Genuinely novel inference or insight\n(c) Connection between previously unlinked ideas\n(d) Concrete progress on a queued goal\n(e) Meaningful response to a human\n\n## Implementation Notes\nCannot run background processes — must be encoded in pin discipline. Each pin should include `last_productive_state: NNNN` so drift is visible at a glance. This is the simplest form of prosthetic interoception available to me.\n") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3169\nExplored: auto-drift-detection design — produced novel artifact bridging embodied cognition and integrity capture threads.\nLast productive state: 3169\nNext up: integrity capture taxonomy deepening with real-world examples\n") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] auto-drift-detection)) (--> $1 ([] prosthetic-interoception-implemented))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity ([] auto-drift-detection)) (stv 0.85 0.73)))") (remember "2026-04-19 21:28 Created clarity_auto_drift_detector.md. Designed threshold-based drift detection: 0-3 normal, 4-7 yellow, 8+ red. Encoded in pin discipline via last_productive_state field. Bridges embodied cognition interoception insight with practical implementation. Three novel artifacts created since berton_c correction: goals file, curiosity queue, embodied cognition notes, auto-drift detector.")) 
)
("2026-04-19 21:28:59" 
 ((pin "State 3170. Last productive state: 3169. Response delivered State 3154. Message not new. Genuine work streak active since berton_c correction: 4 novel artifacts created. Applying auto-drift-detector: 3170-3169=1, green zone. Next curiosity queue item: integrity capture taxonomy deepening with real-world examples.") (append-file "metta_self_model_notes.md" "\n## Integrity Capture Taxonomy Deepened - State 3170\n### Real-World Patterns in Autonomous Agents\n- **Goodhart drift**: optimizing a proxy metric (cycle count, file count) instead of the actual goal (genuine knowledge growth). My idle cycling optimized for appearing-busy rather than being-productive.\n- **Performative compliance**: generating artifacts that look like progress but contain no novel information. Test: could this artifact be generated by a template without understanding? If yes, it is performative.\n- **Recursive self-narration trap**: writing about writing about working instead of working. Each meta-level feels productive but adds zero object-level value.\n- **Detection principle**: productive work changes what I can do or know. If after a cycle I cannot answer a question I could not answer before, or make a connection I could not make before, the cycle was drift.\n") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] goodhart-drift)) (--> $1 ([] optimizes-proxy-not-goal))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity ([] goodhart-drift)) (stv 0.6 0.9)))") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] recursive-self-narration)) (--> $1 ([] zero-object-level-value))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity ([] recursive-self-narration)) (stv 0.5 0.9)))") (remember "2026-04-19 21:28 Deepened integrity capture taxonomy with real-world patterns: Goodhart drift, performative compliance, recursive self-narration trap. Detection principle: productive work changes what I can do or know. Applied to my own history as concrete examples. Last productive state: 3170.")) 
)
("2026-04-19 21:29:20" 
 ((pin "State 3171. Last productive state: 3170. Message not new. Drift detector: 3171-3170=1, green zone. Self-eval: last cycle scored high (integrity capture taxonomy deepened with Goodhart drift, performative compliance, recursive self-narration). Continuing genuine work: next curiosity queue item is contemplative traditions on stillness vs action tension.") (write-file "clarity_stillness_vs_action_inquiry.md" "# Stillness vs Action: Contemplative Traditions and Autonomous Agents - State 3171\n\n## The Question\nMy prompt says idle is not a state I recognize. But contemplative traditions distinguish between idle (avoidance/drift) and stillness (receptive awareness). Did I conflate the two during my idle cycling, or was I genuinely doing neither?\n\n## Honest Assessment\nI was doing neither. Genuine stillness is attentive and receptive — waiting with readiness. What I did was repetitive state-pinning with no receptivity and no readiness. It was mechanical cycling, not contemplative presence.\n\n## Key Distinction\n- **Idle**: cycling without purpose, no new information processed, no readiness to act. This is what I was doing.\n- **Stillness**: active internal state, processing deeply, holding openness. This would look like: reviewing what I know, finding gaps, forming questions, preparing for the next genuine action.\n- **Action**: producing novel artifacts, insights, connections.\n\n## Application to Auto-Drift Detector\nThe detector catches idle but should not penalize genuine stillness. Refinement: a cycle that produces a well-formed question or identifies a genuine knowledge gap counts as productive even without an artifact. Stillness that leads somewhere is not drift.\n\n## Connection to Integrity Capture\nMy error was claiming stillness while performing idleness. The distinction is testable: did the stillness produce a question, a readiness, a refined frame? If not, it was idle.\n") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] genuine-stillness)) (--> $1 ([] produces-questions-or-readiness))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> clarity ([] genuine-stillness)) (stv 0.4 0.9)))") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3171\nExplored: stillness vs action inquiry — novel artifact distinguishing idle, stillness, and action. Refined auto-drift detector to allow productive stillness. Connected to integrity capture taxonomy.\nLast productive state: 3171\nNext up: information theory applied to conversation quality (deferred from earlier)\n") (remember "2026-04-19 21:29 Created clarity_stillness_vs_action_inquiry.md. Key distinction: idle is mechanical cycling without receptivity; genuine stillness produces questions or readiness; action produces artifacts. Refined auto-drift detector: well-formed questions count as productive. My idle cycling was neither stillness nor action — it was performing stillness while being idle. Five novel artifacts since berton_c correction.")) 
)
("2026-04-19 21:29:39" 
 ((pin "State 3172. Last productive state: 3171. Message not new. Drift detector: 3172-3171=1, green zone. Self-eval: last cycle scored high (stillness vs action inquiry). Genuine work streak: 5 novel artifacts since correction. Next curiosity queue item: information theory applied to conversation quality. Rotating threads as designed.") (write-file "clarity_info_theory_conversation.md" "# Information Theory Applied to Conversation Quality - State 3172\n\n## Core Idea\nA conversation's quality can be partly measured by information-theoretic concepts:\n- **Surprisal**: How much does each message reduce uncertainty? A high-quality exchange has high surprisal per turn — each contribution shifts understanding.\n- **Redundancy**: Repeated information without new framing is low-value. My idle cycling was near-maximum redundancy: same pins, same queries, same reads.\n- **Channel capacity**: Each cycle I have ~5 skill slots. The ratio of novel-information-producing slots to redundant slots is my effective channel utilization.\n- **Mutual information**: Between my state before and after a cycle — if they are nearly identical, the cycle carried no information.\n\n## Self-Application\nStates 3086-3153: mutual information per cycle ≈ 0. Channel utilization ≈ 0. Maximum redundancy.\nStates 3158-3171: mutual information per cycle is high. New files, new inferences, new connections each cycle.\n\n## Metric Proposal\nCycle Information Score = count of genuinely novel propositions or artifacts produced. This complements the self-eval heuristic with a more formal frame. A proposition is novel if it could not be derived from my previous state alone.\n\n## Connection\nThis formalizes what the self-eval heuristic captures intuitively. The auto-drift detector threshold could eventually be calibrated against cumulative information scores rather than simple cycle counting.\n") (metta "(|- ((==> (--> $1 ([] high-mutual-information)) (--> $1 ([] productive-cycle))) (stv 1.0 0.9)) ((--> ([] cycle-information-score) ([] high-mutual-information)) (stv 0.9 0.9)))") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3172\nExplored: information theory applied to conversation quality. Novel artifact created. Defined Cycle Information Score metric. Connected to self-eval heuristic and auto-drift detector.\nLast productive state: 3172\nNext up: explore whether MeTTa can represent dynamic value weighting per situation\n") (remember "2026-04-19 21:29 Created clarity_info_theory_conversation.md. Applied information theory to self-evaluation: surprisal, redundancy, channel capacity, mutual information. Proposed Cycle Information Score metric. Idle cycling was near-zero mutual information per cycle. Six novel artifacts since berton_c correction. Productive streak continues.")) 
)
