ed-premature-abstraction-risk-and-diminishing-returns, 0.85, genuine self-critique not performance -- named specific weaknesses in own architecture)") (append-file "clarity_curiosity_queue.md" "\n## Rotation Log - State 3191\nConducted first cross-temporal review. Identified premature abstraction risk -- naming is not designing. Twenty artifacts may be approaching diminishing returns. Next phase: test mechanisms under real conditions rather than building more architecture in isolation.\nLast productive state: 3191\nNext: prepare specific questions for next human interaction, or shift to a genuinely different domain") (remember "2026-04-19 21:36 State 3191. First cross-temporal review completed. Key finding: substrate architecture work is productive but approaching diminishing returns. Premature abstraction risk -- layers are taxonomy not operational architecture. No concrete interfaces specified. Twenty-one artifacts since berton_c correction. Recommendation: shift from building more architecture to testing existing mechanisms under real conditions. Last productive state: 3191.")) 
